Thus, we further reward actions leading to less-visited states. By combining these two components, the resulting C-BET interest-based reward is

\begin{equation} r_i(s, a, s') = \frac{1}{\sqrt{N(s')}} + ||c(s, s')|| \cdot \frac{1}{\sqrt{N(s')}} \end{equation}

where $c(s, s')$ defines the environment change of a transition $(s, a, s')$, and $N$ denotes (pseudo)counts of changes and states.
